                        &lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;br&gt;&lt;/br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/br&gt;Me and the company I work for we would like to host this year event. There was a similar event no longer than a month ago, so we are thinking about changing the original topic for December, so people will would not bugger that we copied the idea or just being bored - because they already solved the GOL problem. So after a quick brain storm we came with an idea, that maybe we could go we some kind of hacathon - with the topic of web browser. We are thinking that maybe we could…&lt;/p&gt;                    </summary>

                                            <content type="html">
                            &lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Me and the company I work for we would like to host this year event. There was a similar event no longer than a month ago, so we are thinking about changing the original topic for December, so people will would not bugger that we copied the idea or just being bored - because they already solved the GOL problem. So after a quick brain storm we came with an idea, that maybe we could go we some kind of hacathon - with the topic of web browser. We are thinking that maybe we could ask people to form a teams up to four people and develop whatever they want, that acually work in any web browser - that shows the power of real time communication between different users of a server; a game through www, a social page, a video player that you can watch the same movie with others, etc.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Or do you think that this is too far from original idea of CR ?&lt;br/&gt;Any ideas and feedback is appreciated.&lt;/p&gt;                        </content>
                    
