                            <entry>
                    <title>Little bit of gamification</title>
                    <link rel="alternate" href="http://coderetreat.org/xn/detail/6456126:Topic:18519"/>
                                        <id>tag:coderetreat.org,2012-12-05:6456126:Topic:18519</id>
                                        <updated>2012-12-05T18:32:25.948Z</updated>
                    
                                            <author>
                            <name>Marian Schubert</name>
                            <uri>http://coderetreat.org/profile/MarianSchubert</uri>
                        </author>
                    
                    <summary type="html">
                        &lt;p&gt;Hi everyone,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&#039;m one of facilitators/organizers of Coderetreat events in Czech Republic. For some time I have been playing with an idea of adding little bit of gamification into Coderetreat events. Idea is pretty simple - each participant will get short checklist at the beginning of the event. Checklist will contain list of activities which he might try to do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Checklist might look like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Pair with stranger…&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;                    </summary>

                                            <content type="html">
                            &lt;p&gt;Hi everyone,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&#039;m one of facilitators/organizers of Coderetreat events in Czech Republic. For some time I have been playing with an idea of adding little bit of gamification into Coderetreat events. Idea is pretty simple - each participant will get short checklist at the beginning of the event. Checklist will contain list of activities which he might try to do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Checklist might look like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Pair with stranger&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&quot;check&quot;&gt;☐☐☐☐☐&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Delete code after session&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&quot;check&quot;&gt;☐☐☐☐☐☐&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Cover most of the code by tests&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&quot;check&quot;&gt;☐&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Make all methods less than 4 lines&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&quot;check&quot;&gt;☐&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Write tests first (before production code)&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&quot;check&quot;&gt;☐&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Don&#039;t touch mouse&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&quot;check&quot;&gt;☐&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Switch navigator/driver role during session&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&quot;check&quot;&gt;☐&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For each row full of checked checkboxes he will get 1 point. But it wouldn&#039;t be used to compete with others. It&#039;s just for his personal use.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Expected benefits:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;nice and short overview of things one might try to achieve&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;gentle reminder of things one shall do in/after each session (delete code)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;it&#039;s easy to compare driver/navigator cards before session so they can choose what to try next&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;it might even be a nice commemorative item from Coderetreat event (pair partners might even sign each other&#039;s card on back side :)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;...&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;HTML version I&#039;m going to use to print cards for upcoming GDCR event in Prague, Czech Republic - &lt;a href=&quot;http://coderetreat.maio.cz/checklist/checklist.html&quot;&gt;http://coderetreat.maio.cz/checklist/checklist.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Beta version of real card &lt;a href=&quot;http://photos.coderetreat.cz/albums/misc&quot;&gt;http://photos.coderetreat.cz/albums/misc&lt;/a&gt; :)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is github repo: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/maio/coderetreat-checklist&quot;&gt;https://github.com/maio/coderetreat-checklist&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Does it sound like good/bad thing to do at Coderetreat? I would appreciate any feedback. After event I&#039;ll share our experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Marian Schubert&lt;/p&gt;                        </content>
                    
